      • convert

        public edu.uci.ics.jung.graph.Tree<org.openrdf.model.URI,org.openrdf.model.URI> convert(edu.uci.ics.jung.graph.DirectedGraph<V,E> graph,
                                                                                        V root,
                                                                                        Map<org.openrdf.model.URI,V> vlookup,
                                                                                        Map<org.openrdf.model.URI,E> elookup)
        Creates a tree using random, unique URIs instead of actual vertices and nodes. The lookup maps are populated with the conversions. NOTE: the Tree can contain duplicates in the sense that different URIs might map to the same vertex/edge.
        Parameters:
        graph - the graph to convert
        root - the root of the tree
        vlookup - a (usually empty) map that will be populated with the uri-to-vertex lookup
        elookup - a (usually empty) map that will be populated with the uri-to-edge lookup
        Returns:
        a valid tree, no matter what
